Level 60 Half Elf Warlord<BR>
The Kindred - Drinal<BR>
<I>...and they cowered in fear for what had so nearly come to pass!</I><BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uaerildroigheann.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aeril Droigheann</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 262<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/17/01 12:56:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=948.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: mob pushing-what is it?</span><hr size=1> The biggest importance is just positioning.  A lot of AE fights have walls that you can hide the casters behind to prevent them from being hit by it.  In these situations, it's important to keep the mob from moving beyond the corner so it's AE doesn't hit the casters.  If you don't have enough damage to make up for CH/gate then you probably won't have enough to push reliably for an interrupt. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=45589">Aeryl Firebrand</a>, Warlord<br>
