<br>
What I like to do is flank.  Surround the mob.  This keeps the mob from moving around so much.  Here's a sample diagram:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
      P
      |
      M
   /      \
P            P
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
In this above diagram, the mob should move towards the meleer doing the least damage, according to my theory.  If players are doing the same melee damage, then the mob shouldn't be moving at all, since all the pushing is getting countered.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
P 
   \
P  -  M  -  P
   /
P
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
In this above diagram, the mob should definitely be moving towards the right.  Though, the amount it's being pushed per second would most likely be the same, if all players are doing equal damage, in this diagram below:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE CODE START--><pre> 
P
   &gt;  M   
P
</pre><!--EZCODE CODE END--><br>
<br>
<br>
I also have rarely interupted a giant in Kael from casting a heal.  It's not good pushing it into a wall, despite popular belief...  I play a shaman and druid and usually run to a corner to gate away from a train and know that the wall will help me channel through the hits.  Been able to escape some trains while pulling old Chardok this way.<br>
<br>
